nodes.title: Partner Central
nodes.description: The Partner Central home page presents a collection of headline sections that highlight recent announcements, marketing insights, product availability, and upcoming partner programs from Cisco, Pure Storage, and Nutanix. Its primary purpose is to give logged‑in resellers a quick overview of the latest news, stories, and resources they need to stay informed and promote the partners’ solutions. The visible features include a series of banner‑style headers for each major update and a central call‑to‑action inviting users to “catch up on all the latest updates, stories, and insights.”

nodes.title: Partner Central
nodes.description: The page is a sales‑data dashboard within Partner Central that lists individual booking opportunities in a tabular view. Its primary function is to let resellers see and filter details of each opportunity—such as names, IDs, customer, segment, type, stage, forecast category, product lineup, and associated reseller or distributor. The main visible sections are the page header with navigation controls (including “View As”) and the comprehensive table that organizes all of these opportunity attributes for quick reference.

nodes.title: Partner Central
nodes.description: The page is a “Sales Data – Bookings” view filtered to the **New Logo** sub‑category, showing a list of opportunity records in a tabular format. Its primary function is to let a logged‑in reseller examine detailed booking information—such as opportunity name, ID, customer, segment, type, stage, forecast category, product lineup, and associated reseller or distributor—so they can track and manage their sales pipeline. Key sections include the top navigation bar (Partner Central, View As, date selector), the page header with the “Sales Data” label, and the main data table that presents each opportunity across the defined columns.

nodes.title: Partner Central
nodes.description: The page presents the **Renewals Data – Bookings** view within Partner Central, displaying a table that lists renewal‑related booking opportunities (currently showing no results). Its primary function is to let partners review and manage renewal bookings tied to their accounts. The layout includes the standard Partner Central header with navigation controls (e.g., “View As”) and a central table area where opportunity details would appear, along with the site footer.
